  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Designing Monaco Editor**\n\nI\'ve made good progress! I\'ve confirmed that the `ShaderCanvas` looks great and is essentially finished. I\'m now focused on building the `ShaderEditor.tsx` component. I\'m excited about exploring a Monaco Editor wrapper specifically for writing HLSL. It seems Monaco already has native support for `hlsl`, which is a relief!\n\n\n**Exploring Monaco Configuration**\n\nI\'m thrilled with Monaco Editor\'s out-of-the-box HLSL support! Specifying `\"hlsl\"` yields excellent code features. I\'m moving toward integrating `@monaco-editor/react`. I\'m also planning custom styling, theming, and error highlighting. I\'m focusing on \"markers\" and how to use them with the `@monaco-editor/react` library to display compiler errors. I\'ll utilize the `useMonaco` hook to set those markers!\n\n\n**Implementing Error Highlighting**\n\nI\'ve got it working! The Monaco editor now shows red squiggles for HLSL compile errors, complete with hover tooltips displaying WebGL compilation error messages. It\'s a fantastic professional feature! Now, I\'m verifying how to best implement this in `ShaderEditor.tsx`. I\'m designing the component with features such as Monaco Editor loading indicators, custom dark theme configuration, and action buttons. I\'m also planning a compilation status header to display success or failure with expandable error messages.\n\n\n"
