  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Confirming Successful Build**\n\nI\'m incredibly pleased to report a flawless first build! Compilation completed without a hitch, and TypeScript checks passed with flying colors, so I have a production-ready application. Now, I will start to double check other files, to confirm there is nothing missing.\n\n\n**Assessing Readiness to Complete**\n\nI\'m now satisfied with the codebase review and the absence of any critical issues. I am ready to complete the project summary for the user. I have confirmed that the final summary will adhere to the specified communication style.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I have designed and built a highly optimized, fully responsive **HLSL Shader Sandbox** (reminiscent of ShaderToy.com but customized for HLSL developers). \n\nThe application is fully structured, type-safe, and builds cleanly. Here is an overview of the core features and design:\n\n- **Interactive WebGL 2 Viewport**: Renders high-fidelity fragment shaders in real-time, utilizing accurate mouse-drag tracking (`iMouse`), sub-second animation delta clocks (`iTime`/`iTimeDelta`), frame-rate counters, and viewport resolution scaling.\n- **Dynamic Transpiler Engine**: Automatically parses HLSL fragment code and transforms it into GLSL ES 3.00 compatible instructions. It maps native HLSL types (e.g. `float3`, `float2x2`), strips return and parameter semantics (e.g. `: SV_Target`, `: TEXCOORD`), rewrites object-oriented sampler syntax (e.g. `.Sample()`), and provides full overload libraries for standard HLSL intrinsics (`lerp`, `frac`, `saturate`, `mul`, `fmod`, `atan2`, `ddx`, `ddy`, `clip`, `rcp`, `rsqrt`, and `mad`).\n- **Professional Monaco Code Editor**: Combines high-end IDE features like bracket matching, code folding, editable font sizes, and a **Live Error Pipeline** that maps WebGL compiler logs directly back to HLSL line numbers, complete with inline squiggles and hover diagnostics.\n- **Procedural Sampler Inputs**: Generates robust, high-frequency procedural textures (white/value noise, retro checker grids, cyan marble waves, and color-ramp stripes) dynamically on HTML5 canvases at startup to completely eliminate third-party network requests or CORS errors.\n- **Curated HLSL Gallery**: Provides multiple starter templates categorized by category and complexity, including:\n  - *Cosmic Plasma Wave* (Beginner, Wave equations & Color warping)\n  - *Raymarched Metallic Sphere* (Intermediate, 3D SDF raymarching, specular shading, soft shadows, and mouse camera rotation)\n  - *Interactive Mandelbrot* (Intermediate, escape-time fractal rendering with drag-to-pan exploring)\n  - *80s Outrun Synthwave* (Advanced, perspective grid planes, distant mountains, sliced sun, and CRT scanlines)\n  - *Liquid Plasma Metal* (Advanced, reflection vector estimations and normal generation)\n  - *Sunlit Water Caustics* (Intermediate, light refraction ripples with bioluminescent dust)\n- **Deep Slate Visual Layout**: Framed inside a high-contrast twilight workspace using Inter display typography and JetBrains Mono monospace readouts."
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 2
      nanos: 254820443
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
